<br>
Chalk it up to inexperience. Anyway, I now realize that if I want to do more raids on any sort of regular basis I'm going to have to join a guild. But the question is which one to join? I have a number of friends in guilds, but they are all small/mid-size guilds that almost never raid – more like social clubs or cooperatives.  <br>
<br>
So I have to look for information on guilds elsewhere.   I'm having a hard time finding any good reference information on guilds and the various options, how big they are, how often they raid, level qualifications for joining, etc.<br>
<br>
I don't want everyone to respond by saying &quot;Woot, my guild is best....&quot;  Cause I'm sure they are all good in their own way.  I’m just looking for a method to evaluate my options.<br>
<br>
Here's what I'm looking for - good sized (mid-large sized) guild where they raid a few times a week but have enough members that they won't get bent if I can't attend more than 2-4 raids a month. Prefer a strong east coast US membership to make scheduling easier.<br>
<br>
I am not looking for a social club, or a guild into the role-playing thing (&quot;Hark, a dwarf strides yonder......&quot; - not my style) or a guild into that whole EQ marriage thing (one more aspect of the game I'll take a pass on - I have a RL wife, sure don't need another one in EQ!!)  Just looking for a large bunch of good, nice, fun players/smart people who like to kill stuff and help each other out when we can.   I don’t want to be one of those people who hop around between guilds, so I want to make a smart choice up front.  <br>
<br>
On to my question:  Have any of you been in this situation and how did you end up selecting a guild? What are the best resources to research the guild options on Saryrn? I know there are a number of ezboards, but I'd rather not visit each and every one.  Are there web sites where most of the guilds post information? Does Verant publish guild lists with sizes?  And lastly since many of you are in guilds and I’m not, what are the more important qualities that you think I should look for in a guild?<br>
<br>
Any insights would be appreciated.<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Roos<br>
Barb Warr 43<br>
Saryrn<br>
