<br>
Person A joins TWC one week before Planes of Power comes out. They earn a crapload of aaxp over a few months. They also get plenty of nice items over the course of several months because they <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>earned</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the points and spent those points.<br>
<br>
Lo and behold person &quot;A&quot; notices several guilds in PoTime.  TWC (or insert any other guild in existence really) has failed to make person &quot;A&quot; want to stay due to wanting to head to PoTime. Person &quot;A&quot; says &quot;the guild sucks, and fuck em. I want to be in PoTime and not dance around in VT.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, TWC did provide gear/services/etc to person &quot;A&quot; but didn't that person also provide something back to the guild? Did person &quot;A&quot; slow a mob? nuke it down? smack it around with a sword? shoot it with arrows? do combines on high end trade skill items? rezz and buff guildmates? etc..... Playing devil's advocate here but what do they owe TWC or whatever guild they were in? Person &quot;A&quot; earned points (sorta like I earn a paycheck) and spent those points (kinda like I spend money on my truck) on what they wanted.<br>
<br>
Maybe I've just been lucky and haven't been in a 100% social guild. Or maybe this dam blond hair is making me interpret what you're saying incorrectly. I would consider myself a social guild type person. I'm yet to be in a guild that says &quot;you must raid x times a week for y hours each raid&quot;. However even when I was in my teens my first guild  (Norrath's Fallen) took a few groups down to the Qeynos catacombs for the Lucias Dress quest. I currently see DragonChow as a social guild but yet last night Derkator the Vindicator and The Idol of Rallos Zek (guild first there) went down (with a hand from several TWC members). A few members got some very nice upgrades over the course of the night. Granted they're not on par with some of the gear coming out of Ssra, tier 4 planes or Vex Thal but were also nothing to sneeze at. <br>
<br>
